# Project Rules for aidd-nextjs

## Technology Stack
- Next.js 16.1.1 with App Router
- React 19.2.3
- TypeScript 5 with strict mode
- Tailwind CSS v4 (via @tailwindcss/postcss)

## Component Guidelines

### Structure
- Always use TypeScript with strict typing
- Use functional components (not class components)
- Define TypeScript interfaces for all component props
- Use optional props with default values when appropriate
- Export components as default exports
- Place all reusable components in `app/components/` directory

### Example Pattern:
```typescript
interface ComponentProps {
  prop1?: string;
  prop2?: number;
}

export default function Component({ 
  prop1 = "default", 
  prop2 = 0 
}: ComponentProps) {
  return (
    // JSX here
  );
}
```

### Naming
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `Hero.tsx`, `ContactForm.tsx`)
- Files: Match component name exactly
- Variables: camelCase
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- Interfaces: PascalCase with descriptive names (e.g., `HeroProps`, `ButtonProps`)

## Styling Rules

### Tailwind CSS Only
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes exclusively for styling
- Never add custom CSS classes to `globals.css` (only keep `@import "tailwindcss";`)
- Use Tailwind's built-in color palette (gray-900, blue-600, etc.)
- Prefer Tailwind's spacing scale (px-4, mb-8, etc.)

### Responsive Design
- Always use Tailwind responsive breakpoints: `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:`
- Mobile-first approach: base styles for mobile, then add breakpoints for larger screens
- Example: `text-5xl md:text-6xl` (small on mobile, larger on desktop)

### Common Patterns
- Use `flex` with `items-center` and `justify-center` for centering
- Use `space-y-*` for vertical spacing between children
- Use `min-h-screen` for full-height sections
- Use gradient backgrounds: `bg-gradient-to-br from-* via-* to-*`

## File Organization

### Directory Structure
```
app/
├── components/     # Reusable React components
├── page.tsx        # Route pages (App Router)
├── layout.tsx      # Root layout
└── globals.css     # Only Tailwind import
```

### Import Paths
- Use relative imports for local files: `'./components/Hero'`
- Use absolute imports with `@/` alias when configured: `'@/components/Hero'`
- Group imports: external packages first, then local imports

## Code Style

### TypeScript
- Always define interfaces for props
- Use `interface` (not `type`) for component props
- Use `Readonly<>` for props in Next.js layouts when appropriate
- Enable strict mode in tsconfig.json

### React/Next.js
- Use arrow functions or regular functions consistently (prefer regular functions for components)
- Use semantic HTML elements (`<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, etc.)
- Add comments for complex logic or non-obvious code
- Keep components focused and single-purpose

### JSX
- Use self-closing tags when possible: `<Hero />` instead of `<Hero></Hero>`
- Format props on multiple lines when there are 2+ props
- Use descriptive prop names

## Best Practices

### Before Committing
- Always check for linter errors: `npm run lint`
- Ensure TypeScript compiles without errors
- Test that the dev server runs: `npm run dev`

### Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Add `alt` text to images
- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3)
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Consider ARIA labels when needed

### Performance
- Use Next.js Image component for images (when needed)
- Optimize Tailwind classes (avoid redundant classes)
- Keep components small and focused

## Next.js App Router Specifics

### Pages
- Use `app/page.tsx` for routes (not `pages/`)
- Each route needs a `page.tsx` file
- Use `layout.tsx` for shared layouts

### Metadata
- Export `metadata` object from `page.tsx` or `layout.tsx`
- Use Next.js Metadata API for SEO

## Common Patterns in This Project

### Hero Component Pattern
- Full-screen centered layout
- Gradient dark background
- Large typography
- Call-to-action button
- Responsive text sizing

### Component Props Pattern
- Optional props with TypeScript `?`
- Default values in function parameters
- Interface defined above component

## Things to Avoid

- ❌ Don't add custom CSS to globals.css (use Tailwind only)
- ❌ Don't use inline styles (use Tailwind classes)
- ❌ Don't create components without TypeScript interfaces
- ❌ Don't use `any` type (use proper types)
- ❌ Don't mix component styles (keep Tailwind consistent)

